40|$|Endolaryngeal {{microscopic}} laryngosurgery (microlaryngosurgery) using {{a direct}} laryngoscope {{is the preferred}} surgical method for treating laryngeal lesions under general anesthesia. However, this method {{does not provide a}} wide-angle view of the larynx and does not allow detailed observations of the ventricle and subglottis of the laryngeal cavity, resulting in <b>blind</b> <b>areas.</b> Video-assisted endoscopic laryngosurgery using a direct laryngoscope and a long transurethral rigid endoscope was therefore utilized to allow clear observations and complete resection of laryngeal lesions in these <b>blind</b> <b>areas.</b> This endoscopic surgical technique is introduced, and clinical cases are presented...|$|R
