50|$|Vision {{restoration}} therapy {{stimulates the}} retina {{of the eye}} using repetitive points of light that flash on a computer screen. These flashing lights are aimed to stimulate {{the border of the}} <b>blind</b> <b>area</b> of a patient's visual field. The repetitive stimulation is used to help promote visual neuroplasticity and ultimately make new neuronal connections to regain and expand the visual field.|$|E
